[
    {
        "content": "<p>While staring at different syntax ideas for the static dispatch discussion, I had this idea and thought I'd put it out there. I think we've talked something like this before around about the module params discussion, but I'm not sure. </p>\n<p>What if instead of declaring a module like so;</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\"><pre><span></span><code>module [\n    Json,\n    utf8,\n    utf8_with,\n    encode_as_null_option,\n]\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>We declare the module and include the types of it's exported functions, like we are declaring it's external \"interface\" or API. The <code>{} -&gt;</code> below is optional, and may not be needed if we removed module params.</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\"><pre><span></span><code>module {} -&gt; {\n    Json,\n    utf8 : Json,\n    utf8_with : {\n        field_name_mapping ?? FieldNameMapping,\n        skip_missing_properties ?? Bool,\n        null_decode_as_empty ?? Bool,\n        empty_encode_as_null ?? EncodeAsNull,\n    } -&gt; Json,\n    encode_as_null_option: {\n        list ?? Bool,\n        tuple ?? Bool,\n        record ?? Bool,\n    } -&gt; EncodeAsNull,\n}\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>Instead of having the type annotations on the definitions, we instead could instead include them in the header (or neither or both I guess). I like how you could look at a header an see it's API for that module just from the types.</p>\n<p>And then the discussion for dispatch on return types could then look like this instead... which looks like normal syntax compared to <code>[</code>, <code>]</code>.</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\"><pre><span></span><code>Encoder a := module {\n    encode : a -&gt; List U8,\n}\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 493707668,
        "sender_full_name": "Luke Boswell",
        "timestamp": 1736908976
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Personally I love it. But I know that might be controversial</p>",
        "id": 493707880,
        "sender_full_name": "Anthony Bullard",
        "timestamp": 1736909094
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>As long as the annotations are optional of course</p>",
        "id": 493708056,
        "sender_full_name": "Anthony Bullard",
        "timestamp": 1736909216
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>May as well throw the others in there in the same style.. </p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Ruby\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">package</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"ss\">random</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s2\">\"https://...tar.br\"</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"no\">Json</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"no\">Option</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"no\">OptionOrNull</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Ruby\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">app</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"ss\">cli</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">platform</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s2\">\"../../basic-cli/platform/main.roc\"</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"ss\">json</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s2\">\"../package/main.roc\"</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"c1\"># use release URL (ends in tar.br) for local example, see github.com/lukewilliamboswell/roc-json/releases</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">main!</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">List</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">Arg</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">Result</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{}</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"no\">Exit</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">I32</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">Str</span><span class=\"o\">]</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 493708107,
        "sender_full_name": "Luke Boswell",
        "timestamp": 1736909271
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>So the pattern for the API is basically <code>&lt;thing&gt; &lt;intputs&gt; -&gt; &lt;outputs&gt;</code></p>",
        "id": 493708195,
        "sender_full_name": "Luke Boswell",
        "timestamp": 1736909314
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>again, with the types being optional</p>",
        "id": 493708383,
        "sender_full_name": "Luke Boswell",
        "timestamp": 1736909457
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Yep and the inputs maybe only existing in some of these</p>",
        "id": 493708402,
        "sender_full_name": "Anthony Bullard",
        "timestamp": 1736909475
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>And put a &lt;name&gt; in between thing and inputs and I love it</p>",
        "id": 493708426,
        "sender_full_name": "Anthony Bullard",
        "timestamp": 1736909510
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I think the downside would be that when I'm looking at the body of the function, it's nice to see the type right above it, and when I'm doing things like adding or removing an arg, it's nice to be able to change both in one place without jumping around</p>",
        "id": 493708604,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1736909634
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I wonder if editor inlay hints could show those types when you're looking at the module export list at the top <span aria-label=\"thinking\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f914\" role=\"img\" title=\"thinking\">:thinking:</span></p>",
        "id": 493708679,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1736909663
    },
    {
        "content": "<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Ruby\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">platform</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"no\">Model</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">init!</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{}</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">Result</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">Model</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[]</span><span class=\"n\">_</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">render!</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">Model</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">RocRay</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">PlatformState</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">Result</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">Model</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[]</span><span class=\"n\">_</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"c1\"># these modules \"exposed\" for the API</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"no\">RocRay</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"no\">Camera</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"no\">Draw</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"no\">Font</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"no\">Keys</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"no\">Mouse</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"no\">Music</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"no\">Network</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"no\">RenderTexture</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"no\">Sound</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"no\">Texture</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"no\">Time</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"c1\"># these are the entrypoints \"exposed\" for the host</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">initForHost!</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">renderForHost!</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 493708689,
        "sender_full_name": "Luke Boswell",
        "timestamp": 1736909667
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"281383\">Richard Feldman</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/304641-ideas/topic/module.20interface.20API.20syntax/near/493708679\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>I wonder if editor inlay hints could show those types when you're looking at the module export list at the top <span aria-label=\"thinking\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f914\" role=\"img\" title=\"thinking\">:thinking:</span></p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>In an editor, sure. But not in git.  And in an editor you could have a code action to sync the signature</p>",
        "id": 493708799,
        "sender_full_name": "Anthony Bullard",
        "timestamp": 1736909760
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>But regardless of the annotation part, I like using {} here</p>",
        "id": 493708874,
        "sender_full_name": "Anthony Bullard",
        "timestamp": 1736909798
    },
    {
        "content": "<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Ruby\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">app</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"ss\">rr</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">platform</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s2\">\"../platform/main.roc\"</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"nb\">rand</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s2\">\"https://github.com/lukewilliamboswell/roc-random/releases/download/0.3.0/hPlOciYUhWMU7BefqNzL89g84-30fTE6l2_6Y3cxIcE.tar.br\"</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"ss\">time</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s2\">\"https://github.com/imclerran/roc-isodate/releases/download/v0.5.0/ptg0ElRLlIqsxMDZTTvQHgUSkNrUSymQaGwTfv0UEmk.tar.br\"</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"no\">Model</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">init!</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">render!</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 493708877,
        "sender_full_name": "Luke Boswell",
        "timestamp": 1736909800
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>It’s a record, not a list</p>",
        "id": 493708885,
        "sender_full_name": "Anthony Bullard",
        "timestamp": 1736909804
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"515757\">Luke Boswell</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/304641-ideas/topic/module.20interface.20API.20syntax/near/493708689\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Ruby\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">platform</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"no\">Model</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">init!</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{}</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">Result</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">Model</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[]</span><span class=\"n\">_</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">render!</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">Model</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">RocRay</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">PlatformState</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">Result</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">Model</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[]</span><span class=\"n\">_</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"c1\"># these modules \"exposed\" for the API</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"no\">RocRay</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"no\">Camera</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"no\">Draw</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"no\">Font</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"no\">Keys</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"no\">Mouse</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"no\">Music</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"no\">Network</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"no\">RenderTexture</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"no\">Sound</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"no\">Texture</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"no\">Time</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"c1\"># these are the entrypoints \"exposed\" for the host</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">initForHost!</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">renderForHost!</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n</code></pre></div><br>\n</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>I wonder if expose a member for the host could be a separate statement type in the header like imports</p>",
        "id": 493709007,
        "sender_full_name": "Anthony Bullard",
        "timestamp": 1736909897
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>record makes sense if they're annotated, but <code>{ len }</code> is shorthand for <code>{ len: len }</code> everywhere else</p>",
        "id": 493709028,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1736909915
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Yeah, the exporter member len is defined as the module member len</p>",
        "id": 493709065,
        "sender_full_name": "Anthony Bullard",
        "timestamp": 1736909947
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Field punning</p>",
        "id": 493709071,
        "sender_full_name": "Anthony Bullard",
        "timestamp": 1736909952
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>You could even allow a rename for export if you wanted</p>",
        "id": 493709081,
        "sender_full_name": "Anthony Bullard",
        "timestamp": 1736909971
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>reasonable point!</p>",
        "id": 493709087,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1736909977
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Chakra did this exactly</p>",
        "id": 493709089,
        "sender_full_name": "Anthony Bullard",
        "timestamp": 1736909978
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>So maybe I’m biased</p>",
        "id": 493709100,
        "sender_full_name": "Anthony Bullard",
        "timestamp": 1736909984
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>But it only had modules</p>",
        "id": 493709201,
        "sender_full_name": "Anthony Bullard",
        "timestamp": 1736910017
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Using a keyword to export things to the host...</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"C++\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">platform</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">...</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">}</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">...</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"k\">import</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">random</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">Random</span>\n<span class=\"k\">import</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">json</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">Json</span>\n<span class=\"k\">export</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">initForHost</span><span class=\"o\">!</span>\n<span class=\"k\">export</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">renderForHost</span><span class=\"o\">!</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">initForHost</span><span class=\"o\">!</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">...</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 493709408,
        "sender_full_name": "Luke Boswell",
        "timestamp": 1736910140
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Seems reasonable and keeps the record semantics consistent</p>",
        "id": 493709481,
        "sender_full_name": "Anthony Bullard",
        "timestamp": 1736910202
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>And you would only see this syntax in one file per platform</p>",
        "id": 493709501,
        "sender_full_name": "Anthony Bullard",
        "timestamp": 1736910230
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I'm a big fan of this syntax since exports all have to be written in one place anyway. And also this feels very structural-typed, which matches with (non opaque) struct and enum behavior</p>",
        "id": 493920640,
        "sender_full_name": "Derin Eryilmaz",
        "timestamp": 1736945881
    }
]